BPMX T has maxed out dilution for year based on the one third of market cap rule in the 100m shelf which is apparently based on the high water market cap for a rolling 60day period eg 372m on 319 So with the 3985124 Dr T has maxed out until we spike significantly above 372m and we are currently at 994m so until we are at least 4x of todays price If however Jones is selling 85m at less than a dollar per share then we could reach the 372m market cap at a price near 2 per share but that still just the zero point market cap would have to be much higher for a raise The key threshold in the shelf offering is the 75m market cap where T could sell all of the remaining 876m of the 100m shelf which would have to be at a price north of 4 per share depending on how many shares are sold to complete the current 85m raise Volume does not indicate Jones is selling yet if they wait for July news there will be less dilution and 75m threshold SP moves up
